# Copy this file to ".env.local" in this same folder to set persistent
# defaults for run_tests.sh, so you don't have to retype DATADIR/TERMINAL
# on every invocation. .env.local is gitignored (these are machine-specific
# paths, not secrets, but they'd just be noise/churn in the repo).
#
# This is sourced as plain bash — set whichever variables you need below.
# An env var already set when you invoke the script still wins over these.
#
# Common case: your actual MT5 data folder (where MetaEditor compiles the
# .ex5 to) is NOT the git repo folder — find it via MT5: File -> Open Data
# Folder. Example:
#
# DATADIR="/c/Users/YOURNAME/AppData/Roaming/MetaQuotes/Terminal/YOUR-TERMINAL-ID"
#
# Only needed if terminal64.exe isn't at the standard install path or
# inside DATADIR itself:
#
# TERMINAL="/c/Program Files/MetaTrader 5/terminal64.exe"
